    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-08T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="42"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./97a: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Chiefs of Diplomatic Missions in the American
                            Republics</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-08T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 8, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President has announced that the Under Secretary of State<note n="12"
                        xml:id="d42fn12">Sumner Welles, Representative of the Secretary of
                        State.</note> will represent the United States at the conference in Panama.
                    He will be assisted by the following as advisers: The Honorable Edwin C. Wilson,
                    Minister Designate to Uruguay; and Dr. Herbert Feis,<note n="13"
                        xml:id="d42fn13">Herbert Feis, Adviser; Adviser on International Economic
                        Affairs, Department of State.</note> Dr. Warren Kelchner,<note n="14"
                        xml:id="d42fn14">Warren Kelchner, Secretary General of the Delegation:
                        Chief, Division of International Conferences, Department of State.</note>
                    and Miss Marjorie M. Whiteman,<note n="15" xml:id="d42fn15">Marjorie M.
                        Whiteman, Legal Adviser; Assistant to the Legal Adviser, Department of
                        State.</note> of the Department of State. Mr. Paul C. Daniels, Foreign
                    Service Officer, will act as secretary to Mr. Welles.<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d42fn16">For a complete list of the delegation of the United States,
                        see <hi rend="italic">Report of the Delegate of the United States of America
                            to the Meeting of the Foreign Ministers of the American Republics Held
                            at Panamá September 23–October 8, 1939</hi> (Washington, Government
                        Printing Office, 1940).</note>
                </p>
                <p>You will please inform the Government to which you are accredited.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
